casebody.data:
JAMES M. MILLER v. CLARENCE G. TILDEN 16 So. (2nd) 433

January Term, 1944

February 1, 1944 Division A G. P. Garrett and H. T. Pool, for appellant. Tilden & Hays and Jackson A. Cargill, for appellee. TERRELL, J.:

The question raised in this case is concluded by our opinion and judgment on rehearing in Tison v. Hyer, et al., decided this date. The judgment appealed from is therefore reversed on authority of the last cited case.

Reversed.

BUFORD, C. J., CHAPMAN and ADAMS, JJ., concur.
